    {# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       OFFICIAL GOVERNMENT SOURCES
       ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
    <h2 class="section-heading">Official Government Sources</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted); font-size:var(--text-sm); margin-bottom:var(--space-6);">Primary sources UPSC trusts. Use these for facts, data, and policy details in your answers.</p>

    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap:var(--space-5); margin-bottom:var(--space-10);">

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">PIB (Press Information Bureau)</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Official press releases — policies, schemes, government decisions. Essential for both Prelims and Mains current affairs.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">PRS Legislative Research</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Bill summaries, Parliament sessions, committee reports. The single best source for GS2 governance and polity questions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Economic Survey &amp; Budget</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Annual economic analysis by DEA. Mandatory reading for GS3 economy questions — data, trends, and policy direction.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">NITI Aayog Reports</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">SDG India Index, State Health Index, development reports. Data-rich source for value additions in Mains answers.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">India Year Book</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Government publication covering all sectors — facts, figures, schemes. Direct source for Prelims factual MCQs.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Yojana &amp; Kurukshetra</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Government magazines with thematic deep dives on development, agriculture, governance. Great for Mains essay material.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    {# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       EXAM STRATEGY
       ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
    <h2 class="section-heading">Exam Strategy — The 3-Phase Approach</h2>

    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap:var(--space-5); margin-bottom:var(--space-6);">

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Phase 1 — Foundation</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">3-4 months: Read NCERTs (6-12) + standard books. Build the conceptual base for all 4 GS papers. Don't jump to answer writing yet.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Phase 2 — Current Affairs</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Ongoing: Daily newspaper reading + editorial analysis. Link static notes with current events. Use <a href="https://ujiyari.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--color-brand); font-weight:600;">Ujiyari.com</a> for daily coverage.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Phase 3 — Answer Writing</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">3-4 months before Mains: Practice 2-3 answers daily. Revise using BharatNotes topic pages. Solve PYQs under timed conditions.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <h2 class="section-heading">Key Habits</h2>

    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap:var(--space-5); margin-bottom:var(--space-8);">

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Daily</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">1 hour current affairs + 1 editorial analysis. Consistency beats volume — 1 hour daily is better than 5 hours on weekends.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Weekly</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">2 answer writing practice sessions + 1 Prelims mock or sectional test. Review mistakes the same day.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Monthly</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Full revision of one GS paper + monthly current affairs compilation. Use BharatNotes as your revision template.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
